Additionally, it may belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category because it specifically compares the performance of recurrent networks (RNNs) and convolutional networks (CNNs). Finally, it may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category because CNNs are commonly used in image processing tasks.
